# Montrroase Next.js Client — Architecture Audit (Full)

## Executive Summary

The codebase is **large, actively growing, and functionally capable**, but has accumulated several structural problems that will increasingly cause bugs, slow development, and make onboarding difficult. The core issue is a **scattered, multi-taxonomy component organisation** that grew organically without a central rule: components are classified simultaneously by *role* (`admin/`, `agent/`, `client/`), by *feature* (`marketing/`, `scheduler/`), by *UI area* (`dashboard/`), and by *portal* (`portal/`, `management/`). These taxonomies overlap and conflict.

---

## 1. Component Directory — Multi-Axis Taxonomy Conflict

The `components/` folder has **18 subdirectories** with no single consistent rule:

```
components/
├── admin/          ← role-scoped
├── agent/          ← role-scoped
├── auth/           ← feature-scoped
├── call/           ← feature-scoped
├── client/         ← role-scoped (1 file only!)
├── common/         ← generic utility
├── dashboard/      ← UI-area-scoped (contains role sub-folders)
├── developer/      ← sub-role scoped
├── management/     ← portal-area scoped
├── marketing/      ← feature-scoped (massive; 28 sub-dirs)
├── messaging/      ← feature-scoped
├── portal/         ← portal-area scoped
├── profile/        ← feature-scoped
├── quotes/         ← feature-scoped
├── scheduler/      ← feature-scoped
├── services/       ← feature-scoped
├── settings/       ← feature-scoped
├── ui/             ← design system primitives
```

> [!WARNING]
> There is no documented rule deciding *when* a component should live in `dashboard/` vs `marketing/` vs `agent/` vs `management/`. This produces three separate systems for the same concept (tasks) split across `components/marketing/tasks/`, `components/management/tasks/`, and `components/agent/scheduling/`.

### Top-Level Loose Files
Four components sit **directly in `components/`** with no folder at all:
- `AboutSectionOptimized.tsx`
- `QuestionnaireWizard.tsx`
- `ServiceSelector.tsx`
- `ServiceSwitcher.tsx`
- `image-carousel.tsx`
- `interactive-glow-background.tsx`
- `masonry-parallax-grid.tsx`

These are marketing/landing-page components that should live in `components/marketing/landing/` or a dedicated `components/sections/` group.

