## 2. Task Management — Three Parallel Implementations

The most acute duplication in the codebase:

| Location | Files | Scope |
|---|---|---|
| `components/marketing/tasks/` | `KanbanBoard`, `TaskCard`, `TaskForm`, `TaskListView`, `TaskTemplateManager` | Agent-marketing basic |
| `components/management/tasks/` | `KanbanColumn`, `TaskCard`, `TaskCardOverlay`, `TaskModal`, `TasksKanbanView`, `TasksListView`, `TaskFilterBar`, `BulkActionBar`, `RecurrenceBuilder`, `ViewToggle`, `RejectionFeedbackPanel` | Management portal (more complete) |
| `components/agent/scheduling/` | `CommandCenter`, `CrossClientTaskList`, `DaySchedule`, `QuickTaskInput`, `RecurringTaskManager`, `RecurringBlockManager`, `WeeklyPlanView`, `TimeBlockEditor`, `FocusTimer` | Scheduling engine |

These three sets share logical concerns (task cards, kanban views, recurring tasks) but are entirely separate implementations. There is a `TaskCard.tsx` in both `marketing/tasks/` and `management/tasks/`.

> [!CAUTION]
> Bug fixes applied to one `TaskCard` will not propagate to the other. New features (e.g. a drag-handle, a priority badge) must be rebuilt in multiple places.

