## 6. `lib/api.ts` — The 2757-Line Monolith

The single `lib/api.ts` file is `~84 KB` and handles authentication, messaging, client management, realtime (Node.js service), group chat, and more. It contains **two different HTTP bases** (`baseURL` for Django, `realtimeBaseURL` for the Node.js service) with almost identical fetch wrappers. A separate `lib/api/` folder exists with split files (`marketing.ts`, `scheduling.ts`, `ads-manager.ts`, etc.) — but `lib/api.ts` itself was not correspondingly decomposed; it still has a commented note:

```
// ============ REMOVED METHODS ============
// ...have been removed as they were part of the deprecated microservices
// For marketing content, use the marketingApi from client/lib/api/marketing.ts
```

The migration *started* but the monolith was left standing. So now there are two data access layers at once.

