## 7. Hooks — Split Between Two Locations

```
hooks/           ← root-level (8 loose hooks)
  useAnalytics.ts
  useBilling.ts
  useContent.ts
  useDashboard.ts
  ...

lib/hooks/       ← library-level (20+ hooks + 3 sub-dirs)
  useAuth.ts
  useScheduling.ts
  useSchedulingEngine.ts
  useClients.ts
  marketing/      ← 14 marketing-specific hooks
  admin/
  developer/
```

Having two hook directories (`hooks/` at the client root and `lib/hooks/`) with no documented distinction between them violates the principle of least surprise. The root-level `hooks/` appears to be legacy; `lib/hooks/` is the live home. Most root-level hooks are empty stubs (0-byte files).

> [!NOTE]
> The zero-byte hook stubs at the root level (`useAnalytics.ts`, `useBilling.ts`, `useContent.ts`, `useDashboard.ts`, `useMessages.ts`, `useNotifications.ts`, `useScrollAnimation.ts`, `useSocialAccounts.ts`) were likely created as placeholders and never implemented. They should either be deleted or completed.

