## 8. `DashboardLayout` — `useEffect` Called After Conditional Return

In `app/dashboard/layout.tsx`:

```typescript
// line 144-153: conditional return
if (loading) {
  return <div>Loading...</div>;   // ← early return
}

// line 156-160: useEffect AFTER early return
useEffect(() => {
  if (!loading && !isAuthenticated && !isGuest) {
    router.replace('/auth/login');
  }
}, [loading, isAuthenticated, isGuest, router]);
```

> [!CAUTION]
> This is a **violation of the Rules of Hooks**. A `useEffect` must not be called after a conditional return. React will throw a "rendered more hooks than previous render" error if `loading` transitions from `true` to `false`. The redirect logic must be moved *before* the loading guard or handled inside the loading block.

