## 9. `DashboardLayout` — `setInterval` Polling for `localStorage`

```typescript
// dashboard/layout.tsx lines 117-126
const interval = setInterval(() => {
  const collapsed = localStorage.getItem('sidebar-collapsed');
  if (collapsed) setSidebarCollapsed(JSON.parse(collapsed));
  ...
}, 100);
```

A `setInterval` running every 100ms is polling `localStorage` to sync sidebar state between the root layout and a nested portal. This is called "same-window storage sync" — but it fires **10 times per second** for the entire lifetime of the dashboard session.

> [!CAUTION]
> This is a significant performance concern and an architectural smell. The correct solution is to use React Context or Zustand to share sidebar state between the global layout and the management portal, eliminating the need for localStorage polling altogether.

