## 11. Admin Sidebar Linking to Client Routes

In the admin navigation (sidebar.tsx lines 172–186):

```typescript
company: [
  {
    href: '/dashboard/client/marketing',  // ← CLIENT route from ADMIN nav
    label: 'Marketing',
    ...
  },
  { href: '/dashboard/client/website-builder', label: 'Website', ... },
],
```

Admin nav links point to `/dashboard/client/*` routes. This means the admin is navigating into the **client portal** to view their own marketing assets. This is a semantic problem — admin's company marketing view should be an admin-scoped route, not reusing the client portal. If the client route requires role === 'client' guards, this will silently fail.

---

## 12. `components/client/` — Nearly Empty

`components/client/` contains only **one file**: `PhaseCountdownCard.tsx`. Meanwhile all client-facing dashboard components live in `components/dashboard/client/`. This makes the `components/client/` folder misleading — it implies client-specific components but almost nothing is there.

